article.description: — Tariq Francis' 22 points helped NJIT defeat UMBC 75-74 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Francis scores 22 as NJIT downs UMBC 75-74
article.linkText: Francis scores 22 as NJIT downs UMBC 75-74
article.story: BALTIMORE -- — Tariq Francis' 22 points helped NJIT defeat UMBC 75-74 on Saturday night. Francis had nine rebounds for the Highlanders (5-14, 1-6 America East Conference). Kjell de Graaf scored 18 points and added seven rebounds and three blocks. Adam Hess shot 4 for 9, including 3 for 6 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points. The Highlanders snapped a six-game skid. Marcus Banks led the Retrievers (6-15, 1-5) in scoring, finishing with 21 points and eight rebounds. Dion Brown added 18 points for UMBC. Franck Emmou also recorded 17 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
